premium formula with natural “The Mother,” easy to take, vinegar-free taste or smell, and 98% fat free. The Mother is a special fermentation process that preserves natural benefits for digestion, gut health, and immunity. Benefits - Helps control blood sugar and cholesterol levels after meals. - Support a longer-lasting feeling of fullness and reducing overall food intake - Boost probiotics for gut health and protect gastrointestinal infections Key Ingredients - Apple Cider Vinegar 1200 mg. - Consist of 120 mg. acetic acid - Contain The Mother Directions and Warnings DIRECTIONS : 1 tablet together or after the meal WARNINGS : Patients with gastritis or acid reflux should consult a doctor. Children and pregnant women should not consume. Do not use in weight control or reduction purposes. Should eat a variety of the five categories of food in appropriate proportions. STORAGE : Store below 25C, in a cool, dry place. Do not use, if cap seal is broken. Reasons to love us We have been developing science-based formulas using premium ingredients sourced from around the world for over 50 years. We believe in natural ingredients being our hero ingredients. We also pursue the latest research findings to formulate our advanced product ranges and consistently strive to anticipate consumer demand. Backed by science Premium quality formula 50+ year heritage Certified B-Corp We are B-Corp Certified B Corps are for-profit companies that meet high standards of social and environmental performance, transparency, and accountability. Swisse is a brand of H&H Group, a certified B Corp. We feel honoured to be part of a global community using business as a force for good. Frequently Asked Questions Do we need to take vitamin supplements? The key is to ensure that we get a complete and balanced intake of nutrients each day. However, due to lifestyle limitations and dietary choices, we may not always receive the necessary nutrients in adequate amounts. In such cases, dietary supplements can be beneficial. Can Swisse products be taken alongside medication or medical treatments? Each individual has different nutritional and medicinal needs. If you are unsure whether Swisse products are suitable for you, it is best to consult a doctor. Please note that dietary supplements do not prevent, alter, or replace medical treatment or a well-balanced diet. What is the best time to take vitamins? Some supplements work best when taken with food, while others are more effective on an empty stomach. It is essential to follow the instructions on the label to maximize the benefits of each product. How long do dietary supplements last? In general, dietary supplements have a shelf life of approximately two years from the manufacturing date. Where does Swisse source its ingredients? We carefully select and source high-quality, premium-grade ingredients from around the world to ensure that only the best components go into our products. Where are Swisse products manufactured? Most of our products are manufactured in Australia. Please refer to the product packaging for the specific country of origin. The recommended dosage on the label applies to which age group? The recommended dosage is intended for individuals aged 18 and above. You may also like Swisse Ultibiotic Daily Active Probiotic Sale price 1,850 ฿ Swisse Lecithin Sale price 900 ฿ Our Products Beauty Eye Care Gut Health Gummies Immunity Joints, Bones, & Muscles Multivitamins Super Fruits & Herbs Skincare About Swisse Our Story Ingredients Help & Support FAQs Contact Us Privacy Policy Follow Us &copy; Swisse Thailand , 2026 Choosing a selection results in a full page refresh.\n\nBenefits of Apple Cider Vinegar in a convenient tablet. Each serving provides 120 mg of Acetic Acid and natural “The Mother” to support digestion, gut health, and immunity — without the strong vinegar taste. Sale price 790 ฿\n\nKey Ingredients - Apple Cider Vinegar 1200 mg. - Consist of 120 mg. acetic acid - Contain The Mother\n\nDirections a