wallow tablets are suitable for adults with increased magnesium needs, including those with low dietary intake or high physical demands. Taken as directed, Blackmores MagMin offers targeted support to help meet daily magnesium requirements. Product Format Tablet Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Muscle Health Bone Health No Added Gluten No Added Wheat No Added Dairy Benefits & How To Use Benefits Highly bioavailable magnesium. Helps prevent dietary magnesium deficiency. Supports muscle function. Maintains bone health. Supports body metabolism. Small tablet, making it easier to swallow. Dosage Adults: To help prevent magnesium deficiency; Women - 9 tablets per day in divided doses with meals (no more than 3 tablets at any one time). Men - 11 tablets per day in divided doses with meals (no more than 3 tablets at any one time). Children under 18 Only as prescribed by a health professional. Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Supplements may only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. If symptoms persist talk to your health professional. If you are pregnant or breastfeeding, talk to your health professional before use. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains sulfites. Benefits Dosage Warnings Highly bioavailable magnesium. Helps prevent dietary magnesium deficiency. Supports muscle function. Maintains bone health. Supports body metabolism. Small tablet, making it easier to swallow. Adults: To help prevent magnesium deficiency; Women - 9 tablets per day in divided doses with meals (no more than 3 tablets at any one time). Men - 11 tablets per day in divided doses with meals (no more than 3 tablets at any one time). Children under 18 Only as prescribed by