criptionTh":null,"extractedText":"Blackmores Conceive Well™ Gold All Products Shop All Products New Products Best Sellers Vegan Certified Women&#x27;s Health Men&#x27;s Health Kid&#x27;s Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition By Category Arthritis, Joint & Bone Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutritional Oils Heart Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition Kids&#x27; Health Men&#x27;s Health Multivitamins Muscle Support Nails, Hair & Skin Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health By Ingredient Calcium CoQ10 Curcumin Echinacea Fish Oil & Omega 3 Glucosamine Iron Magnesium Probiotics Selenium Vitamin B Vitamin C Vitamin D Vitamin E Zinc Health Hub By Categories By Type Latest Articles Action Plans Arthritis, Bone & Joint Beauty & Skincare Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutrition Oils Heart & Cardiovascular Health Kids & Infant Health Men&#x27;s Health Muscle Support & Fitness Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Recipes Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health Action Plans Articles Recipes Latest Articles About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Pillars Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Contact us Ask A Naturopath Our Newsroom Blackmores Subscribe Search Home Chevron Icon Horizontal products Chevron Icon Horizontal Blackmores Conceive Well™ Gold Size Size 28 capsules + 28 tablets Good health changes everything—start your pregnancy journey with Blackmores Conceive Well™ Gold. Formulated for women planning to conceive, it supports preconception health, maternal health, and female reproductive system health. Taken daily from at least one month before conception, it helps prepare the body for pregnancy and supports healthy foetal development. This formula also contains folic acid, which helps prevent neural tube defects such as spina bifida, and iodine to support healthy foetal brain development. With key nutrients including iron and omega-3s, it’s designed to support you through one of life’s most important stages. Product Format Capsule Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Conception Foetal Development No Added Wheat No Added Gluten No Added Yeast No Added Dairy Benefits & How To Use Benefits Pregnancy is one of the most nutritionally demanding periods you can go through. Pregnancy increases your need for certain vitamins and minerals that are essential to support the development of a healthy baby (recommended daily intakes increase during pregnancy). It is important for women who are trying for a baby to maintain a healthy, well-balanced diet in combination with a pre-pregnancy supplement. Doing so will help provide your body with the essential nutrients it needs to help with a healthy pregnancy. Blackmores Conceive Well™ Gold helps prepare the body for pregnancy, through: Supplying nutrients that support the female reproductive system and pre-conception health. Providing nutrients to support healthy foetal development. Dosage Adults Take 1 capsule and 1 tablet once a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Ideally taken up to six months before conception. Once you fall pregnant stop using this product and switch to Blackmores Pregnancy and Breast-Feeding Gold. Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Additional supplements may be needed when you are pregnant, discuss your individual requirements with your health professional. WARNING – Stop taking this medication if you experience tingling, burning or numbness and see your healthcare practioner as soon as possible [contains vitamin B6]. This medicine contains selenium which is toxic in high doses. A daily dose of 150 micrograms for adults of selenium from dietary supplements should not be exceeded. Do not take while on warfarin therapy without medical advice. Do not exceed the stated dose except on medical advice. If you have had a baby with a neural tube defect/spina bifiba, seek specific medical advice. Advise your doctor of any medicine you take during pregnancy, particularly in your first trimester. If you are concerned about the health of yourself or your baby, talk to your health practitioner. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains fish, soya bean products and sulfites. Benefits Dosage Warnings Pregnancy is one of the most nutritionally demanding periods you can go through. Pregnancy increases your need for certain vitamins and minerals that are essential to support the development of a healthy baby (recommended daily intakes increase during pregnancy). It is important for women who are trying for a baby to maintain a healthy, well-balanced diet in combination with a pre-pregnancy supplement. Doing so will help provide your body with the essential nutrients it needs to help with a healthy pregnancy. Blackmores Conceive Well™ Gold helps prepare the body for pregnancy, through: Supplying nutrients that support the female reproductive system and pre-conception health. Providing nutrients to support healthy foetal development. Adults Take 1 capsule and 1 tablet once a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Ideally taken up to six months before conception. Once you fall pregnant stop using this product and switch to Blackmores Pregnancy and Breast-Feeding Gold. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Additional supplements may be needed when you are pregnant, discuss your individual requirements with your health professional. WARNING – Stop taking this medication if you experience tingling, burning or numbness and see your healthcare practioner as soon as possible [contains vitamin B6]. This medicine contains selenium which is toxic in high doses. A daily dose of 150 micrograms for adults of selenium from dietary supplements should not be exceeded. Do not take while on warfarin therapy without medical advice. Do not exceed the stated dose except on medical advice. If you have had a baby with a neural tube defect/spina bifiba, seek specific medical advice. Advise your doctor of any medicine you take during pregnancy, particularly in your first trimester. If you are concerned about the health of yourself or your baby, talk to your health practitioner. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains fish, soya bean products and sulfites. The Blackmores Difference Ingredients Active ingredients per tablet: Potassium iodide 197 micrograms eqivalent to iodine 150 micrograms Folic acid 500 micrograms Cupric sulfate anhydrous 3.3 mg equivalent copper 1.3 mg Riboflavin (vitamin B2) 1.5 mg Thiamine nitrate 1.5 mg equivalent thiamine (vitamin B1) 1.2 mg Manganese sulfate monohydrate 15.4 mg equivalent manganese 5 mg Zinc sulfate monohydrate 41.6 mg equivalent zinc 15 mg Nicotinamide 20 mg Ferrous fumarate 75.4 mg equivalent iron 24 mg Pyridoxine hydrochloride 50 mg equivalent pyridoxine (vitamin B6) 41.2 mg Cyanocobalamin (vitamin B12) 50 micrograms Heavy magnesium oxide 350 mg equivalent magnesium 200 mg Ascorbic acid (vitamin C) 200 mg Calcium ascorbic dihydrate 363 mg equivalent ascorbic acid (vitamin C) 300 mg Total vitamin C 500 mg Selenomethionine 161 micrograms equivalent selenium 65 micrograms Biotin 100 micrograms Calcium pantothenate 5 mg equivalent pantothenic acid (vitamin B5) 4.6 mg Active ingredients per capsule: Fish oil - natural 500 mg containing omega-3